{
  "What is the purpose of scientific notation?": "",
  "To make numbers harder to read and compare": "",
  "To express very large or very small numbers in a compact form": "",
  "To convert numbers from one unit to a different unit": "",
  "To round numbers to the nearest whole integer value": "",
  "Scientific notation is a way to write very large or very small numbers compactly using a coefficient multiplied by a power of 10. For example, 300,000,000 m/s becomes 3 × 10⁸ m/s, which is much easier to write and compare.": "",
  "Which number is correctly written in scientific notation?": "",
