  "What does 'order of magnitude' mean in science?": "",
  "The exact value of a measurement taken in the laboratory": "",
  "The power of 10 closest to a number, showing its general size": "",
  "The number of decimal places in a measured value overall": "",
  "The sequence in which scientific operations must be performed": "",
  "Order of magnitude refers to the power of 10 nearest to a value, giving a rough idea of how big or small something is. For instance, 5,000 has an order of magnitude of 10³, while 50,000 has an order of magnitude of 10⁴.": "",
